# HCDE 530 Week 2 Project Rules

This project is a small class assignment with Python, CSV data, and a static HTML dashboard.

## Scope
- Apply these rules to all edits in this repository.

## Coding Preferences
- Keep code beginner-friendly and readable.
- Prefer clear variable names and small, direct functions.
- Add short comments only when logic is not obvious.
- Avoid adding heavy dependencies unless explicitly requested.

## Python (`demo_word_count.py`)
- Keep logic simple and standard-library only.
- Use UTF-8 file handling and preserve current CSV column names.
- If changing output, keep summary stats (total, shortest, longest, average).

## Data (`demo_responses.csv`)
- Do not modify existing rows unless explicitly asked.
- Preserve header order: `participant_id, role, response`.

## Dashboard (`dashboard.html`)
- Keep it single-file and framework-free (HTML/CSS/JS only).
- Ensure it still reads `demo_responses.csv` from the same folder.
- Keep visual style clean and accessible (high contrast, legible text).

## Git Safety
- Do not run destructive git commands (e.g., force push, hard reset) without explicit user approval.
- Keep commits focused and use clear, plain-language messages.
